00:07:22.510 --> 00:07:24.700
because I just don't remember.

00:07:24.700 --> 00:07:25.930
They have a good fact there.

00:07:25.930 --> 00:07:30.880
That Neanderthals could
communicate in a way

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:34.240
that, there is a lion and
this lion is dangerous,

00:07:34.240 --> 00:07:38.110
we should be aware
of it, and that's it.

00:07:38.110 --> 00:07:44.380
Dangerous lion, we fight him,
or we escape, or we hide.

00:07:44.380 --> 00:07:47.320
But what Homo sapiens
made, they went further.

00:07:47.320 --> 00:07:53.110
They created things like, lion
can be a symbol of our forest.

00:07:53.110 --> 00:07:56.290
Or lion, he's a
defender of our forest--

00:07:56.290 --> 00:08:00.400
which actually, from the point
of matter of fact, is bullshit.

00:08:00.400 --> 00:08:04.870
I mean, a lion cannot
be anybody but lion.

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:07.450
But human beings,
somehow, created

00:08:07.450 --> 00:08:09.250
this kind of abstract thinking.

00:08:09.250 --> 00:08:12.520
And their language
allowed them to imagine

00:08:12.520 --> 00:08:13.930
things that don't exist.

00:08:13.930 --> 00:08:21.790
That consequently led
to myths and religion.

00:08:21.790 --> 00:08:25.600
And that actually made
possible to gather

00:08:25.600 --> 00:08:27.409
large groups of people.

00:08:27.409 --> 00:08:29.200
Much more than hundreds
of people, but even

00:08:29.200 --> 00:08:31.270
thousands of people together.

00:08:31.270 --> 00:08:37.210
You cannot stick together just
because you live in some area.

00:08:37.210 --> 00:08:41.710
Because people lived
in small tribes--

00:08:41.710 --> 00:08:44.140
100, 200 people.

00:08:44.140 --> 00:08:47.590
But when you share the common
beliefs, or the common things--

00:08:47.590 --> 00:08:51.400
like for example, that a lion
is a master of the forest--

00:08:51.400 --> 00:08:55.810
it makes your bodies in the
other forest understandable.

00:08:55.810 --> 00:08:59.830
And you can communicate, and
then that makes strong bonds.

00:08:59.830 --> 00:09:03.850
And actually, this made
Homo sapiens so powerful.

00:09:03.850 --> 00:09:05.210
They could create tribes--

00:09:05.210 --> 00:09:07.750
not of hundreds of people,
but thousands of people.

00:09:07.750 --> 00:09:14.350
And that's how they literally
exterminated all their rivals.

00:09:14.350 --> 00:09:22.570
So that will be the second
fundamental invention, which is

00:09:22.570 --> 00:09:25.270
language and abstract thinking.

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:27.940
The third is the
only one I didn't

00:09:27.940 --> 00:09:29.200
