00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:25.480
You can argue about whether
Christianity or Islam,

00:10:25.480 --> 00:10:27.010
or some other
religions, are better.

00:10:27.010 --> 00:10:29.110
Or some people don't
believe in God.

00:10:29.110 --> 00:10:30.950
But nobody argues about money.

00:10:30.950 --> 00:10:33.580
I mean, it's very
hard to find somebody

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:37.840
except Shaolin monks, who
just don't use money--

00:10:40.750 --> 00:10:42.850
Money changed everything.

00:10:42.850 --> 00:10:44.980
Money changed
behavior of people.

00:10:44.980 --> 00:10:47.080
And they made them more--

00:10:47.080 --> 00:10:51.400
When we say materialistic,
it's not only bad thing,

00:10:51.400 --> 00:10:55.980
it's something that
you become cautious.

00:10:55.980 --> 00:10:57.780
Money makes people cautious.

00:10:57.780 --> 00:10:59.880
And probably it
also preserved us

00:10:59.880 --> 00:11:03.150
from doing or making
some big mistakes

00:11:03.150 --> 00:11:04.860
at the beginning of our history.

00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:10.840
Also money are,
unfortunately, pushing

00:11:10.840 --> 00:11:13.300
us to make big, big
mistakes, huge mistakes,

00:11:13.300 --> 00:11:16.090
now in this part of our history.

00:11:16.090 --> 00:11:18.040
But anyway money
is number three.

00:11:18.040 --> 00:11:20.010
Number four is writing.

00:11:20.010 --> 00:11:23.170
And writing is
obvious invention,

00:11:23.170 --> 00:11:26.410
but many things
existed before writing.

00:11:26.410 --> 00:11:30.040
For example, oral
narratives allowed people

00:11:30.040 --> 00:11:32.260
to have, once again, religion.

00:11:32.260 --> 00:11:35.609
To have myths, to have
tales-- fairy tales.

00:11:35.609 --> 00:11:36.400
To have everything.

00:11:36.400 --> 00:11:41.860
But what created writing, it
created very important things

00:11:41.860 --> 00:11:45.040
like law and science.

00:11:45.040 --> 00:11:49.140
Because law is something
that should be--

00:11:49.140 --> 00:11:53.100
you cannot treat it very
free, in a very free way.

00:11:53.100 --> 00:11:57.960
You should know it, for
sure, how to use this law.

00:11:57.960 --> 00:12:02.730
And narrative is very
rarely strict and precise.

00:12:02.730 --> 00:12:05.340
Narrative can be--
I can say what

00:12:05.340 --> 00:12:10.680
law is, you will say this to
somebody else, the same thing

00:12:10.680 --> 00:12:11.880
but with distortion.

00:12:11.880 --> 00:12:14.870
And finally, somebody
not in this room,

00:12:14.870 --> 00:12:17.280
but in the other
room, will completely

00:12:17.280 --> 00:12:18.670
hear the different thing.

00:12:18.670 --> 00:12:22.170
So writing allows us
to see the same things.

00:12:22.170 --> 00:12:24.960
And when we create
a judiciary system,

00:12:24.960 --> 00:12:30.300
we talk about law, it's a
must to know exactly the same

00:12:30.300 --> 00:12:32.370
that other people
know about these laws.

00:12:32.370 --> 00:12:35.235
Suddenly signs and history
also started to develop.

00:12:37.950 --> 00:12:42.090
Because you also save
a lot of your memory,

00:12:42.090 --> 00:12:44.970
not for remembering all the
things that all your ancestors

00:12:44.970 --> 00:12:48.540
created, but just doing all
your mundane and routine stuff

00:12:48.540 --> 00:12:51.210
knowing that you can find
somewhere in a library

00:12:51.210 --> 00:12:52.170
or whatever.

00:12:52.170 --> 00:12:55.170
Suddenly the beginning
of creation of writing,

00:12:55.170 --> 00:12:57.210
there were only a few
people in the world--

00:12:57.210 --> 00:12:59.760
a few small percentage
of the world--

00:12:59.760 --> 00:13:12.830
who had access to this to
this cave with precious gems,

00:13:12.830 --> 00:13:13.750
or whatever.

00:13:13.750 --> 00:13:15.260
How we call knowledge.

00:13:15.260 --> 00:13:20.070
But generally, it started
changing the world as well.

00:13:20.070 --> 00:13:23.100
And the fifth, in
my opinion is--

00:13:23.100 --> 00:13:24.950
We already talked
about religion.

00:13:24.950 --> 00:13:26.960
We could say that
religion is an invention.

00:13:26.960 --> 00:13:30.800
But religion wasn't a true
invention because religion--

00:13:30.800 --> 00:13:34.010
It took us thousands of years--
more and more and more--

00:13:34.010 --> 00:13:36.980
to come from just
primitive beliefs,

00:13:36.980 --> 00:13:40.260
to myths, to fairy tales, and
then to religion as we know it.

00:13:40.260 --> 00:13:45.740
But there was one concrete,
and one specific invention,

00:13:45.740 --> 00:13:47.840
where we talk about
religion, which

00:13:47.840 --> 00:13:53.930
really changed the history
and the path of development

00:13:53.930 --> 00:13:54.930
of human being.

00:13:54.930 --> 00:13:56.900
Which is monotheism.

00:13:56.900 --> 00:13:59.270
Because monotheism,
which was created,

00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:08.000
some argue, in Egypt, the end
of their ruling 1,200 years

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:09.230
before Christ.

00:14:09.230 --> 00:14:14.760
Some say that it was
created by Jewish people

00:14:14.760 --> 00:14:16.500
when they create a Judaism.

00:14:16.500 --> 00:14:20.190
We don't actually need
to understand exactly.

00:14:20.190 --> 00:14:23.880
What we need to understand, that
for the first time in history

00:14:23.880 --> 00:14:26.310
abstract thinking--

00:14:26.310 --> 00:14:27.870
sort of that high--

00:14:27.870 --> 00:14:34.890
that people created the idea of
invisible and transcendent god,

00:14:34.890 --> 00:14:36.630
who is omnipotent.

00:14:36.630 --> 00:14:38.447
And who also is very--

00:14:42.870 --> 00:14:45.450
God cannot do bad things.

00:14:45.450 --> 00:14:51.840
That's a big, big
difference from religion

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:52.860
that we had before.

00:14:52.860 --> 00:14:55.860
For example, if you
talk about Greek gods.

00:14:55.860 --> 00:14:58.530
Greek gods were very
much like people.

00:14:58.530 --> 00:15:00.150
They behaved like people.

00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:01.090
They cheated.

00:15:01.090 --> 00:15:02.070
They killed.

00:15:02.070 --> 00:15:07.820
They did all the sins
that we people do.

00:15:07.820 --> 00:15:12.720
And actually, in ancient
pre-monotheism culture

00:15:12.720 --> 00:15:16.980
it was still bad to kill
people, or to do some bad stuff.

00:15:16.980 --> 00:15:20.490
But it was bad just
mostly because when

00:15:20.490 --> 00:15:24.720
you kill people, when
you kill somebody,

00:15:24.720 --> 00:15:26.160
you would be killed as well.

00:15:26.160 --> 00:15:30.060
Or you would be punished
because you deprived some family

00:15:30.060 --> 00:15:32.010
of labor force, or whatever.

00:15:32.010 --> 00:15:35.720
But monotheism, and Judaism,
and Christianity, and Islam,

00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:38.160
created moral.

00:15:38.160 --> 00:15:43.560
So when we started believing
that to kill, or to steal,

00:15:43.560 --> 00:15:48.910
or to cheat, is not bad just
because you violate some law,

00:15:48.910 --> 00:15:51.120
but it's bad because it's bad.

00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:55.170
And it is something that makes
your psyche suffer, and makes

00:15:55.170 --> 00:15:58.920
your soul suffering,
and you feel bad.

00:15:58.920 --> 00:16:07.560
And actually, this is
very obvious thing now.

00:16:07.560 --> 00:16:08.970
So what about that?

00:16:08.970 --> 00:16:11.910
We can think that moral
existed for all other time,

00:16:11.910 --> 00:16:12.610
but it's not.

00:16:12.610 --> 00:16:13.560
But it doesn't.

00:16:13.560 --> 00:16:14.280
It didn't.

00:16:14.280 --> 00:16:17.700
It exists only for
2,000 or 3,000 years.

00:16:17.700 --> 00:16:19.620
Before that, moral
was different,

00:16:19.620 --> 00:16:21.270
if it existed at all.

00:16:21.270 --> 00:16:28.760
So what we now have, we behave
not only in a practical way,

00:16:28.760 --> 00:16:31.220
and not only in an
instinctive way.

00:16:31.220 --> 00:16:34.010
Instinctive way as
a way of animals.

00:16:34.010 --> 00:16:36.020
Practical way is
something the human

00:16:36.020 --> 00:16:39.650
being created, even
before monotheism emerged.

00:16:39.650 --> 00:16:42.350
But what we call spiritual way--

00:16:42.350 --> 00:16:44.630
or way of the conscious--

00:16:44.630 --> 00:16:48.590
is something that this idea
that was probably first--

00:16:48.590 --> 00:16:55.910
or one of the first times
described in ten commandments,

00:16:55.910 --> 00:16:58.490
which we know from the Bible--

00:16:58.490 --> 00:17:00.170
is a fundamental thing.

00:17:00.170 --> 00:17:03.020
It also gave people
a freedom of choice.

00:17:03.020 --> 00:17:07.940
So it described a human
being as a creature

00:17:07.940 --> 00:17:15.589
which was granted by God
with freedom of choice.

00:17:15.589 --> 00:17:19.910
And freedom of choice, either
to violate commandments or not.

00:17:19.910 --> 00:17:21.500
To do this, or to do that.

00:17:21.500 --> 00:17:24.349
So we are free to
do whatever we want,

00:17:24.349 --> 00:17:28.430
but we know that at the end
we'll pay the price for that.

00:17:28.430 --> 00:17:33.580
Or we'll be rewarded for that.

00:17:33.580 --> 00:17:38.750
It changed human beings
behavior, I think, for good.

00:17:38.750 --> 00:17:41.810
Because now we're
different people

00:17:41.810 --> 00:17:44.910
than we were 2,000 or
3,000 thousand years ago.

00:17:44.910 --> 00:17:47.050
So these five
inventions, I think

00:17:47.050 --> 00:17:48.440
they are the most important.

00:17:48.440 --> 00:17:57.550
Because they framed
what we are now.

00:17:57.550 --> 00:18:02.390
And they framed our development
for the next 1,000 years.

00:18:02.390 --> 00:18:06.700
The inventions I will be talking
later, they are more practical,

00:18:06.700 --> 00:18:12.580
but they wouldn't be
possible without these five.

00:18:12.580 --> 00:18:16.150
Fire gun weapon--
it's much later.

00:18:16.150 --> 00:18:20.890
I put it as an invention,
as a separate invention.

00:18:20.890 --> 00:18:23.620
I'm not talking
about cold weapon.

00:18:23.620 --> 00:18:27.010
Because cold weapon--
even animals, even ape

00:18:27.010 --> 00:18:29.500
used stones for fighting.

00:18:29.500 --> 00:18:33.700
And it took us thousands of
years to come to good swords.

00:18:33.700 --> 00:18:42.820
And to have all these weapons
of destruction that Greeks,

00:18:42.820 --> 00:18:44.620
and Romans, and Chinese used.

00:18:44.620 --> 00:18:51.940
But what fire gun weapon did,
it equalized possibilities

00:18:51.940 --> 00:18:57.490
and military power
of rivals, or enemies

00:18:57.490 --> 00:19:00.330
of people who fight each other.

00:19:00.330 --> 00:19:02.860
Of states who fight each other.

00:19:02.860 --> 00:19:05.640
And, as you know,
fire gun weapon--

00:19:05.640 --> 00:19:07.830
although was it was
created in China--

00:19:07.830 --> 00:19:11.400
but mostly developed
at the beginning

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:13.500
of the end of Middle
Ages and beginning

00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:15.510
of Renaissance in Europe.

00:19:15.510 --> 00:19:23.790
And finally it came to the point
when wars became unbearable.

00:19:23.790 --> 00:19:29.070
So at the beginning a big
country a lot of military force

00:19:29.070 --> 00:19:31.560
could conquer, easily,
a smaller country.

00:19:31.560 --> 00:19:35.670
And just because they
came with horses and were

00:19:35.670 --> 00:19:39.390
swords, and it was very
difficult to fight them.

00:19:39.390 --> 00:19:42.750
But then, with fire
guns, and with mortars,

00:19:42.750 --> 00:19:53.280
and with all these cannons, it's
much easier to defend yourself.

00:19:53.280 --> 00:19:59.580
And the last war that showed
us the probably impossibility

00:19:59.580 --> 00:20:06.150
of a former order, was a
Thirty Years' War in Europe,

00:20:06.150 --> 00:20:09.120
that finally ended up with
Westphalia Peace, which

00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:10.770
created modern states.

00:20:10.770 --> 00:20:15.390
Because modern states is
something that we understand

00:20:15.390 --> 00:20:18.810
as granted, although some
people question this now even

00:20:18.810 --> 00:20:20.070
in 2000's.

00:20:20.070 --> 00:20:21.160
We know about that.

00:20:21.160 --> 00:20:25.150
But modern state, a
state with borders,

00:20:25.150 --> 00:20:27.300
which is respected
by other states, no

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:31.830
matter how small or how weak
it is, once it's recognized,

00:20:31.830 --> 00:20:32.940
it's recognized.

00:20:32.940 --> 00:20:35.730
Before Thirty Years' War,
there was no notion like that.

00:20:35.730 --> 00:20:37.800
Empires could do
whatever they wanted.

00:20:37.800 --> 00:20:40.530
Big kingdoms, they
conquered smaller kingdoms

00:20:40.530 --> 00:20:42.990
and acquired them
and did everything.

00:20:42.990 --> 00:20:47.580
But now after Westphalia
Peace in 1648,

00:20:47.580 --> 00:20:51.450
people started treating
states differently.

00:20:51.450 --> 00:20:55.890
And the main reason for
that was that to fight wars

00:20:55.890 --> 00:21:00.950
became very, very difficult,
and costful, and just--

00:21:00.950 --> 00:21:05.060
Two million people died
during these three decades,

00:21:05.060 --> 00:21:06.360
and nobody won.

00:21:06.360 --> 00:21:07.130
Nobody.

00:21:07.130 --> 00:21:08.700
It was still status quo.

00:21:08.700 --> 00:21:12.080
So they just came
to the point where

00:21:12.080 --> 00:21:14.790
they say we need to start
from the very beginning.

00:21:14.790 --> 00:21:18.350
So if not the fire gun,
we wouldn't have had that.

00:21:18.350 --> 00:21:21.230
Afterwards, some
scientific stuff.

00:21:25.570 --> 00:21:31.550
Printing led to Protestantism,
as a consequence

00:21:31.550 --> 00:21:33.280
to scientific and
industrial evolution

00:21:33.280 --> 00:21:34.480
in northern countries.

00:21:34.480 --> 00:21:38.440
Because printing made
knowledge affordable,

00:21:38.440 --> 00:21:42.820
both in figurative
and direct meaning.

00:21:42.820 --> 00:21:45.160
We started reading
books massively.

00:21:45.160 --> 00:21:49.630
We started reading books in our
languages, they got printed.

00:21:49.630 --> 00:21:54.280
And it was much easier to
read books than before.

00:21:54.280 --> 00:21:55.990
You didn't need to know Latin.

00:21:55.990 --> 00:22:00.490
And you didn't need to go to the
church to ask for permission.

00:22:00.490 --> 00:22:07.240
If you had enough money,
you could buy these books.

00:22:07.240 --> 00:22:11.200
And in 200 years after
printing was invented,

00:22:11.200 --> 00:22:17.140
northern Europe was already
booming and developing

00:22:17.140 --> 00:22:19.660
technologies and science.

00:22:19.660 --> 00:22:24.970
Then discovery of
America by Europeans

00:22:24.970 --> 00:22:29.380
also changed the
framework, and also changed

00:22:29.380 --> 00:22:31.480
what the world is now.

00:22:31.480 --> 00:22:37.530
You know that probably Chinese
could have discovered America.

00:22:37.530 --> 00:22:41.370
They actually started
creating expeditions

00:22:41.370 --> 00:22:45.270
during 15th century, but
they abruptly stopped them.

00:22:45.270 --> 00:22:47.070
Nobody knows why.

00:22:47.070 --> 00:22:48.900
Their ships were much bigger.

00:22:48.900 --> 00:22:52.600
Their potency was much
stronger magnitude.

00:22:52.600 --> 00:22:59.760
Their [INAUDIBLE] was way
better than these first Columbus

00:22:59.760 --> 00:23:01.740
ships, they were really small.

00:23:01.740 --> 00:23:04.240
But somehow Europeans
managed to do that.

00:23:04.240 --> 00:23:07.050
And finally, it
led to the creation

00:23:07.050 --> 00:23:09.570
of big European empires.

00:23:09.570 --> 00:23:14.850
Who afterwards, through
missionaries, and also trade

00:23:14.850 --> 00:23:21.620
companies, first enforced
the whole world to accept--

00:23:21.620 --> 00:23:28.580
and then probably also promoted
with much milder means--

00:23:28.580 --> 00:23:31.160
European way of
thinking, mindset.

00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:33.620
And actually added it to life.

00:23:33.620 --> 00:23:38.420
And nowadays we still have the
societies who think different.

00:23:38.420 --> 00:23:43.670
But mostly European,
or I would say,

00:23:43.670 --> 00:23:47.600
northern European practical
way of treating life,

00:23:47.600 --> 00:23:49.910
is dominating in the world now.

00:23:49.910 --> 00:23:56.060
And who knows if Chinese
discovered America what

00:23:56.060 --> 00:23:57.720
the world would have been now.

00:23:57.720 --> 00:23:58.980
We don't know.

00:23:58.980 --> 00:24:00.860
We just know that
it was Europeans.

00:24:00.860 --> 00:24:02.150
It was Columbus.

00:24:02.150 --> 00:24:08.540
And finally, it's an interesting
irony, and very important

00:24:08.540 --> 00:24:09.770
historical irony.

00:24:09.770 --> 00:24:13.910
You probably know
that Columbus--

00:24:13.910 --> 00:24:17.150
it was possible to organize
this expedition because Columbus

00:24:17.150 --> 00:24:25.520
came to Spanish kings,
Ferdinand and Isabella in 1492.

00:24:25.520 --> 00:24:27.710
It was the third time
he asked them for money.

00:24:27.710 --> 00:24:29.750
Two times before they refused.

00:24:29.750 --> 00:24:33.140
And 1492, they say OK,
we'll give you money.

00:24:33.140 --> 00:24:34.700
We have money now.

00:24:34.700 --> 00:24:37.450
Who knows why.

00:24:37.450 --> 00:24:40.210
Some of you know
why it was 1492.

00:24:40.210 --> 00:24:45.160
Why they couldn't do
that 1483, or something?

00:24:45.160 --> 00:24:51.290
That was exactly the year
that Spanish kings finally

00:24:51.290 --> 00:24:58.130
reconquered the last part of
Iberian Peninsula from Arabs.

00:24:58.130 --> 00:25:05.860
And that year they
took Grenadian

00:25:05.860 --> 00:25:09.840
where well a lot of Arabic
and Jewish rich people,

00:25:09.840 --> 00:25:11.270
and they got all this money.

00:25:11.270 --> 00:25:12.860
And they ruined all the stuff.

00:25:12.860 --> 00:25:14.870
And these were money
that they started

00:25:14.870 --> 00:25:17.570
using in their next endeavors.

00:25:17.570 --> 00:25:20.810
And actually, Arab
and Jewish money

00:25:20.810 --> 00:25:24.860
created a new Christian power.

00:25:24.860 --> 00:25:28.430
And it's ironic, but that's
how sometimes history

00:25:28.430 --> 00:25:30.710
is being done.

00:25:30.710 --> 00:25:33.500
Then some scientific inventions.

00:25:33.500 --> 00:25:37.880
Newton created his famous
laws, and Newton's mechanics,

00:25:37.880 --> 00:25:40.970
and it changed the
attitude to facts.

00:25:40.970 --> 00:25:44.960
Before Newton's
laws mostly people

00:25:44.960 --> 00:25:50.875
believed that faith,
matter of faith,

00:25:50.875 --> 00:25:53.780
was much more important
than matter of fact.

00:25:53.780 --> 00:25:56.000
And Newton's laws
were the first time

00:25:56.000 --> 00:26:01.760
when we could predict exactly,
without any divine force,

00:26:01.760 --> 00:26:08.750
that if the ball is at point A
now that it will be in a point

00:26:08.750 --> 00:26:12.170
B. And we knew 100% exactly.

00:26:12.170 --> 00:26:16.610
And it made people belief
in fact very powerful.

00:26:16.610 --> 00:26:19.760
And when we started
believing in facts,

00:26:19.760 --> 00:26:26.180
we started thinking in
this more practical way.

00:26:26.180 --> 00:26:29.900
And that how science
and industry developed.

00:26:29.900 --> 00:26:32.030
And that's why England,
and other northern European

00:26:32.030 --> 00:26:35.300
countries, started
proceeding and developing

00:26:35.300 --> 00:26:36.740
so fast afterwards.

00:26:36.740 --> 00:26:40.340
Facts, and matter of
facts, became dominating.

00:26:40.340 --> 00:26:42.560
In other parts of the world,
especially for example,

00:26:42.560 --> 00:26:45.410
in the part of the
world where most of us

00:26:45.410 --> 00:26:49.700
are from, Eastern Europe,
or for example, Asia--

00:26:49.700 --> 00:26:53.090
people didn't believe in
facts long afterwards.

00:26:53.090 --> 00:26:56.360
So it took us probably 200
or 300 years afterwards.

00:26:56.360 --> 00:27:01.850
Because societies like ours were
mainly transcendent and driven

00:27:01.850 --> 00:27:06.920
by irrational things like faith.

00:27:06.920 --> 00:27:09.230
And some spiritual things.

00:27:09.230 --> 00:27:12.860
English people became very
practical-- and in a good way,

00:27:12.860 --> 00:27:13.430
cynical--

00:27:13.430 --> 00:27:15.020
much earlier.

00:27:15.020 --> 00:27:18.140
And they started
to do achievements

00:27:18.140 --> 00:27:21.890
in practical fields,
mostly because of science.

00:27:21.890 --> 00:27:25.850
And Newton was the first, who
was the first person who opened

00:27:25.850 --> 00:27:29.860
this door of matter of fact.

00:27:29.860 --> 00:27:32.360
The direct consequence
of that, but I

00:27:32.360 --> 00:27:35.000
think it's a single and
a separate invention,

00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:37.220
was a steam machine of wood.

00:27:37.220 --> 00:27:41.210
Because steam machine of
wood created modern industry.

00:27:41.210 --> 00:27:45.120
Manifold time increased
labor power used by man.

00:27:45.120 --> 00:27:46.580
And productivity, also.

00:27:46.580 --> 00:27:49.310
And reduced cost
of productivity.

00:27:49.310 --> 00:27:51.440
And liberated a
great amount of labor

00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:53.630
force to do the
other job, like then

00:27:53.630 --> 00:27:56.390
to be peasants in the fields.

00:27:56.390 --> 00:27:59.420
So it created plants,
factories and everything.

00:27:59.420 --> 00:28:04.130
Actually, the second
invention which

00:28:04.130 --> 00:28:11.210
also was a consequence of
this scientific revolution,

00:28:11.210 --> 00:28:12.620
was electricity.

00:28:12.620 --> 00:28:16.010
And James Maxwell, a
Scottish scientist,

00:28:16.010 --> 00:28:20.300
a very modest guy, who
was thinking, creating,

00:28:20.300 --> 00:28:21.800
working on electricity.

00:28:21.800 --> 00:28:24.920
Theoretically, he
created his Maxwell laws,

00:28:24.920 --> 00:28:35.210
which allowed us to create
many things that we see now.

00:28:35.210 --> 00:28:37.460
I don't think that LED's--

00:28:37.460 --> 00:28:43.460
but probably just our electric
lights, or everything--

00:28:43.460 --> 00:28:45.050
what electricity created.

00:28:45.050 --> 00:28:50.240
And funny thing is, when
these laws were discovered

00:28:50.240 --> 00:28:52.610
and written first in
scientific papers,

00:28:52.610 --> 00:28:55.520
most scientists didn't
accept them well.

00:28:55.520 --> 00:29:01.100
So it took probably 20 or 30
years before Maxwell theory

00:29:01.100 --> 00:29:06.830
proved its practical
value and made

00:29:06.830 --> 00:29:10.920
all of us using electricity.

00:29:10.920 --> 00:29:14.940
Three medical inventions
happened during these times.

00:29:14.940 --> 00:29:17.790
First was very important--

00:29:17.790 --> 00:29:20.820
and it happened even
before or, probably

00:29:20.820 --> 00:29:23.970
approximately the same time,
when Newton created his laws--

00:29:23.970 --> 00:29:28.470
and it was invention,
or creation, or the idea

00:29:28.470 --> 00:29:29.970
of blood circulation.

00:29:29.970 --> 00:29:32.400
It was made by English
scientist Harvey,

00:29:32.400 --> 00:29:35.500
and he first
understood that blood

00:29:35.500 --> 00:29:40.170
is circulating from arteries
to capillaries, and then

00:29:40.170 --> 00:29:41.760
through veins, back.

00:29:41.760 --> 00:29:46.770
And actually, you may ask
why is it so important?

00:29:46.770 --> 00:29:49.680
It is so important because
it gave us the idea what

00:29:49.680 --> 00:29:54.270
really blood is for our body.

00:29:54.270 --> 00:29:56.910
And it also gave
us the possibility

00:29:56.910 --> 00:30:02.080
to heal and cure some diseases,
and some really bad things

00:30:02.080 --> 00:30:04.380
with our bodies that
we couldn't do before.

00:30:04.380 --> 00:30:08.670
For example, we understood
that gangrene is,

00:30:08.670 --> 00:30:13.620
and all blood inflammations,
they cause deaths.

00:30:13.620 --> 00:30:17.340
And they knew how to treat
it afterwards much easier.

00:30:17.340 --> 00:30:19.740
But two inventions,
medical inventions,

00:30:19.740 --> 00:30:23.080
that came later in the
beginning of the 20th century,

00:30:23.080 --> 00:30:30.000
they even changed our life
even more rapid, and more

00:30:30.000 --> 00:30:31.050
significant way.

00:30:31.050 --> 00:30:33.720
These are vaccines
and antibiotics.

00:30:33.720 --> 00:30:39.020
The first killed viruses,
the second killed bacterias.

00:30:39.020 --> 00:30:44.720
And if vaccines helped us
to stop epidemics of plague,

00:30:44.720 --> 00:30:47.880
and of Spanish flu--

00:30:47.880 --> 00:30:51.530
all this kind of stuff--

00:30:51.530 --> 00:30:53.700
and it helped in
a peaceful life,

00:30:53.700 --> 00:31:01.970
then antibiotics helped
in healing and curing

00:31:01.970 --> 00:31:06.890
wounded people, who were
wounded and injured during wars.

00:31:06.890 --> 00:31:11.810
And in first World War,
which Americans, or Irish,

00:31:11.810 --> 00:31:14.600
or British, called
Great War, people just

00:31:14.600 --> 00:31:17.660
died because of
inflammation all the time.

00:31:17.660 --> 00:31:21.880
Because they got everything.

00:31:21.880 --> 00:31:29.540
They got pneumonia, they
got serious injuries,

00:31:29.540 --> 00:31:32.270
nobody could get cure it.

00:31:32.270 --> 00:31:38.870
But after antibiotics and
vaccines were invented,

00:31:38.870 --> 00:31:42.320
the life expectancy
raised twice.

00:31:42.320 --> 00:31:45.530
So at the beginning of the 20th
century it was 40 years, now

00:31:45.530 --> 00:31:48.660
it's 75, or 70,
average in the world.

00:31:48.660 --> 00:31:50.540
It's almost twice.

00:31:50.540 --> 00:31:55.100
And I think these two
interventions probably

00:31:55.100 --> 00:31:58.760
made a major contribution
to this fact.

00:32:02.360 --> 00:32:07.780
If we talk about later
20th century inventions,

00:32:07.780 --> 00:32:09.590
it's long distance connections.

00:32:09.590 --> 00:32:11.210
Telegraph, telephone, and radio.

00:32:11.210 --> 00:32:12.430
It's actually one invention.

00:32:12.430 --> 00:32:15.160
We don't need to say
that it's three of them.

00:32:15.160 --> 00:32:16.910
It created mass culture.

00:32:16.910 --> 00:32:19.870
It created possibility to--

00:32:19.870 --> 00:32:25.250
it made world flatter,
even before internet.

00:32:25.250 --> 00:32:28.670
It didn't make world flat,
but it made it flatter.

00:32:28.670 --> 00:32:33.470
And it was the first step in
the whole bunch of inventions

00:32:33.470 --> 00:32:34.970
that were coming later.

00:32:34.970 --> 00:32:38.240
But many things, like
radio, created pop music.

00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:44.360
Radio created our first
political debates.

00:32:44.360 --> 00:32:47.420
Radio created, like an
old telephone connect.

00:32:47.420 --> 00:32:49.700
Connected all people
and relatives.

00:32:49.700 --> 00:33:02.710
And it changed--
how to say this?

00:33:02.710 --> 00:33:04.930
I mean, they changed
the way that we

00:33:04.930 --> 00:33:07.150
treated each other,
friends and families.

00:33:07.150 --> 00:33:10.000
For example, if you
have your phone,

00:33:10.000 --> 00:33:13.210
you don't need to see
your parents every day,

00:33:13.210 --> 00:33:15.340
or every week, you
just call them.

00:33:15.340 --> 00:33:19.000
And then that
somehow alienates us.

00:33:19.000 --> 00:33:20.890
And that's not a good thing.

00:33:20.890 --> 00:33:22.690
But that's something
that telephone,

00:33:22.690 --> 00:33:25.390
and other long distance
connection created.

00:33:25.390 --> 00:33:30.640
We started changing
our everyday behavior.

00:33:30.640 --> 00:33:35.410
Quantum mechanics, which
actually, probably some of you

00:33:35.410 --> 00:33:37.030
know.

00:33:37.030 --> 00:33:40.930
Quantum mechanics was created by
a very young scientist of age,

00:33:40.930 --> 00:33:45.400
from 20 to 25, at the
turn of the 20th century.

00:33:45.400 --> 00:33:50.170
And quantum mechanics makes
the job of all of you possible.

00:33:50.170 --> 00:33:52.300
If not that, I
think there will be

00:33:52.300 --> 00:33:58.270
no computers, no internet, no
Google, no this room, nothing.

00:33:58.270 --> 00:34:02.020
Because that's where
everything started.

00:34:02.020 --> 00:34:04.990
Three or four young scientists
in Germany, England,

00:34:04.990 --> 00:34:10.510
and Austria, were so dare to say
that all the science they knew

00:34:10.510 --> 00:34:18.389
before was completely bullshit,
and it didn't describe

00:34:18.389 --> 00:34:23.449
the world of atoms, molecules,
and electrons, and particles.

00:34:23.449 --> 00:34:27.110
So they created this new
science, which actually,

00:34:27.110 --> 00:34:31.010
also, is a very important
cornerstone of civilization

00:34:31.010 --> 00:34:33.150
of human beings.

00:34:33.150 --> 00:34:37.460
Because it needs changing
of our perception.

00:34:40.230 --> 00:34:43.790
It changed our perception
of what is matter of fact.

00:34:43.790 --> 00:34:46.550
Because quantum mechanics is
actually something we cannot

00:34:46.550 --> 00:34:48.650
understand by our brain.

00:34:48.650 --> 00:34:50.480
If some of you, many
of you understand

00:34:50.480 --> 00:34:51.500
what I'm talking about.

00:34:51.500 --> 00:34:52.625
Some of you probably don't.

00:34:52.625 --> 00:34:53.630
I'll explain.

00:34:53.630 --> 00:34:57.740
Quantum mechanics says that
particle-- let's say electron--

00:34:57.740 --> 00:35:02.610
can, if you see a big, big
house with 10 entrances--

00:35:02.610 --> 00:35:07.100
So electron enter all these
entrances simultaneously.

00:35:07.100 --> 00:35:13.730
Not being divided into
parts, being as a whole,

00:35:13.730 --> 00:35:15.875
and you can find it in
each of these entrances,

00:35:15.875 --> 00:35:18.440
at the same time,
and we'll be there.

00:35:18.440 --> 00:35:19.850
So we cannot understand that.

00:35:19.850 --> 00:35:22.580
I mean, our brain
is not quantum.

00:35:22.580 --> 00:35:23.540
It is classical.

00:35:23.540 --> 00:35:25.970
So we cannot understand.

00:35:25.970 --> 00:35:30.290
How can it be possible that
one particle can be present

00:35:30.290 --> 00:35:34.910
at the same moment of time, not
being divided in 10 entrances,

00:35:34.910 --> 00:35:38.240
and it can enter
these entrances,

00:35:38.240 --> 00:35:40.430
and there's still one particle.

00:35:40.430 --> 00:35:44.630
But the truth is that
that's how the world works.

00:35:44.630 --> 00:35:51.120
So it requires from us not
to understand, but to believe

00:35:51.120 --> 00:35:52.370
in power effects.

00:35:52.370 --> 00:35:56.880
To believe in experiments more
than an our analytical skills.

00:35:56.880 --> 00:35:59.670
And it's something that
changed the science at all.

00:35:59.670 --> 00:36:04.290
Because before that
what we did was--

00:36:04.290 --> 00:36:08.875
we first made experiment, then
we started to understand that,

00:36:08.875 --> 00:36:09.750
and then we started--

00:36:09.750 --> 00:36:10.320
OK.

00:36:10.320 --> 00:36:13.680
If our understanding corresponds
with our experiment, OK.

00:36:13.680 --> 00:36:15.450
That's a good explanation.

00:36:15.450 --> 00:36:19.740
But quantum mechanics, for the
first time, when we believe in

00:36:19.740 --> 00:36:23.940
experiment even if we don't
understand how it works.

00:36:23.940 --> 00:36:27.450
And that's a very
important thing.

00:36:27.450 --> 00:36:33.650
Because the fact, and the power
of fact rules now our brains.

00:36:33.650 --> 00:36:36.780
Before that, our brains
ruled everything.

00:36:36.780 --> 00:36:40.550
That's why we saw that
the world was flat

00:36:40.550 --> 00:36:45.890
and we couldn't believe
that our globe was round.

00:36:45.890 --> 00:36:52.130
And we couldn't believe
that we our Earth

00:36:52.130 --> 00:36:54.770
was rotating around sun.

00:36:54.770 --> 00:36:59.000
We thought it was vice versa.

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:00.260
Because that was our brain.

00:37:00.260 --> 00:37:02.740
Or our analytical
skills told us.

00:37:02.740 --> 00:37:06.530
But quantum mechanics
changed it completely.

00:37:06.530 --> 00:37:09.950
And suddenly, after
quantum mechanics

00:37:09.950 --> 00:37:18.300
a couple of inventions that
we see now became possible.

00:37:18.300 --> 00:37:20.550
Television.

00:37:20.550 --> 00:37:23.220
Television, actually-- the
biggest impact television

00:37:23.220 --> 00:37:27.370
had was, in my opinion,
it was not a pop culture.

00:37:27.370 --> 00:37:28.800
But it was politics.

00:37:28.800 --> 00:37:32.070
Because politics
created new politicians.

00:37:32.070 --> 00:37:34.800
Created much bigger populism.

00:37:34.800 --> 00:37:46.710
And when we now
regret about the times

00:37:46.710 --> 00:37:49.530
when we had a big
political leaders,

00:37:49.530 --> 00:37:56.290
and now we have just mediocre
politicians, one of the things

00:37:56.290 --> 00:37:57.610
is television.

00:37:57.610 --> 00:38:05.520
Because television gave
politicians possibility

00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:10.470
not to talk person to
person, but then just to make

00:38:10.470 --> 00:38:11.550
one appearance.

00:38:11.550 --> 00:38:14.760
To say some primitive things
but to be very energetic.

00:38:14.760 --> 00:38:18.030
And to be very persuasive.

00:38:18.030 --> 00:38:19.950
And people started
believing in that.

00:38:19.950 --> 00:38:20.970
And that's how--

00:38:20.970 --> 00:38:24.240
Populism was
present in the world

00:38:24.240 --> 00:38:27.050
before, way long
before television.

00:38:27.050 --> 00:38:31.800
But television made
it an absolution.

00:38:31.800 --> 00:38:36.590
And then, atomic energy, it's
the third revolution in energy

00:38:36.590 --> 00:38:38.670
after steam and electricity.

00:38:38.670 --> 00:38:42.450
I don't need to say about
good and bad impacts of that.

00:38:42.450 --> 00:38:46.140
Chernobyl and Hiroshima
are one of the bad impacts,

00:38:46.140 --> 00:38:48.900
but there are some also
good because it gives us

00:38:48.900 --> 00:38:51.360
a great amount of energy.

00:38:51.360 --> 00:38:55.410
And the last three
inventions, 18, 19, and 20, I

00:38:55.410 --> 00:38:57.600
will not explain it
to you because you

00:38:57.600 --> 00:38:59.190
