00:46:27.320 --> 00:46:28.580
AUDIENCE: Hi Slava.

00:46:28.580 --> 00:46:31.490
You've briefly touched on
the subject of education

00:46:31.490 --> 00:46:32.776
and how it needs to change.

00:46:32.776 --> 00:46:34.400
And I know your dad
was very passionate

00:46:34.400 --> 00:46:36.320
about education
system and change,

00:46:36.320 --> 00:46:37.860
as I was the witness of it.

00:46:37.860 --> 00:46:40.130
So my question is,
how would you like

00:46:40.130 --> 00:46:43.700
to see the education
system develop and progress

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:45.680
into 21st century?

00:46:45.680 --> 00:46:48.440
And what changes would
you like to see first?

00:46:48.440 --> 00:46:49.580
Thank you.

00:46:49.580 --> 00:46:52.280
SLAVA VAKARCHUK: In my opinion,
the most important today

00:46:52.280 --> 00:46:57.260
is not to give information to
children, which you are already

00:46:57.260 --> 00:46:59.030
here in Google are doing.

00:46:59.030 --> 00:47:03.660
So, probably you can have
one or two rivalries,

00:47:03.660 --> 00:47:08.040
which I think is always good
for competition and for quality.

00:47:08.040 --> 00:47:09.720
You still don't have.

00:47:09.720 --> 00:47:13.770
But that's something we
need to leave behind.

00:47:13.770 --> 00:47:22.660
What we need to do is to teach
children how to live lives.

00:47:22.660 --> 00:47:23.910
How to live.

00:47:23.910 --> 00:47:27.400
That is, how to
be a personality.

00:47:27.400 --> 00:47:30.520
How to analyze.

00:47:30.520 --> 00:47:32.350
How to percept.

00:47:32.350 --> 00:47:33.550
How to perceive.

00:47:33.550 --> 00:47:37.060
How to get, and how to give.

00:47:37.060 --> 00:47:42.790
These things, that many thousand
years were abandoned, now,

00:47:42.790 --> 00:47:46.000
little by little, are
starting to come closer.

00:47:46.000 --> 00:47:49.940
And in some education systems,
they already dominate.

00:47:49.940 --> 00:47:51.950
In the best universities
in the world,

00:47:51.950 --> 00:47:54.820
that's what they
teach students now.

00:47:54.820 --> 00:47:58.330
But in some countries,
we still in this--

00:47:58.330 --> 00:48:03.770
I wouldn't say in Ice
Age, or Stone Age--

00:48:03.770 --> 00:48:07.790
but it's still a lot
of things to be done.

00:48:07.790 --> 00:48:11.310
So, I believe we
need to come to shift

00:48:11.310 --> 00:48:16.770
our focus from information
to a personality.

00:48:20.165 --> 00:48:22.590
SPEAKER: Who else?

00:48:22.590 --> 00:48:25.020
Ahh.

00:48:25.020 --> 00:48:25.830
You can throw it.

00:48:25.830 --> 00:48:27.080
It's throwable.

00:48:27.080 --> 00:48:28.040
It's like a game.

00:48:28.040 --> 00:48:28.580
SLAVA VAKARCHUK: Throw it.

00:48:28.580 --> 00:48:29.190
It's fine.

00:48:29.190 --> 00:48:29.505
SPEAKER: Throw it.

00:48:29.505 --> 00:48:30.004
Throw it.

00:48:30.004 --> 00:48:31.987
Don't worry about this.

00:48:31.987 --> 00:48:32.820
AUDIENCE: Hi, Slava.

00:48:32.820 --> 00:48:34.650
Just a quick question--
that you mentioned

00:48:34.650 --> 00:48:36.150
that the invention
of money made us

00:48:36.150 --> 00:48:38.532
a bit more cautious,
for instance.

00:48:38.532 --> 00:48:39.990
Several of the
things you mentioned

00:48:39.990 --> 00:48:42.450
are about creating narratives,
and new narratives.

00:48:42.450 --> 00:48:44.640
And how we should
believe stuff that we

00:48:44.640 --> 00:48:46.230
haven't believed before.

00:48:46.230 --> 00:48:48.554
Considering that,
especially in the West,

00:48:48.554 --> 00:48:50.220
you're getting more
and more constrained

00:48:50.220 --> 00:48:54.570
by economic circumstances by the
time you get to the age of 20

00:48:54.570 --> 00:48:59.910
and 30, how do you see that
tension between material safety

00:48:59.910 --> 00:49:03.240
and the need to challenge
the status quo, playing out

00:49:03.240 --> 00:49:06.455
for our generation afterwards?

00:49:06.455 --> 00:49:08.580
Would people have enough
freedom to actually create

00:49:08.580 --> 00:49:13.034
a new narrative without fearing
for their material well-being?

00:49:13.034 --> 00:49:14.700
SLAVA VAKARCHUK:
That's a good question,

00:49:14.700 --> 00:49:18.200
and what we are
facing now is actually

00:49:18.200 --> 00:49:24.480
the struggle between our
fears and our desires.

00:49:24.480 --> 00:49:28.810
And because we see it
in Western Europe--

00:49:28.810 --> 00:49:31.080
probably Western Europe
and Northern America

00:49:31.080 --> 00:49:35.400
are pioneers in this
new environment--

00:49:35.400 --> 00:49:38.680
we're going to live
some period of time.

00:49:38.680 --> 00:49:44.550
I don't have an
answer about what

00:49:44.550 --> 00:49:48.270
will be the end, or
consequence, or impact of that.

00:49:48.270 --> 00:49:49.140
I don't have it.

00:49:49.140 --> 00:49:55.970
I just know that, somehow,
people during the last 30,000

00:49:55.970 --> 00:50:00.880
years of their history
were managed to create

00:50:00.880 --> 00:50:03.580
a proper way to handle it.

00:50:03.580 --> 00:50:06.850
Sometimes this is not
probably the best way.

00:50:06.850 --> 00:50:08.300
You could find better.

00:50:08.300 --> 00:50:14.260
But it's still as a
river, or a small creek,

00:50:14.260 --> 00:50:17.080
it somehow finds its path.

00:50:17.080 --> 00:50:20.920
And I believe that European--

00:50:20.920 --> 00:50:23.860
and generally, not only
European but human being's

00:50:23.860 --> 00:50:26.430
civilization--
will find its path.

00:50:26.430 --> 00:50:31.490
That the side effect
of civilization

00:50:31.490 --> 00:50:34.990
is that it makes
us more anxious.

00:50:34.990 --> 00:50:37.390
And makes us more stressed.

00:50:37.390 --> 00:50:46.860
And if the biggest problem
of our ancestors in Stone Age

00:50:46.860 --> 00:50:50.665
was a fear to get
eaten by a lion.

00:50:50.665 --> 00:50:53.760
If the biggest fear of
our Middle Aged colleagues

00:50:53.760 --> 00:50:59.910
was to get sick and
die from plague,

00:50:59.910 --> 00:51:04.710
so now our biggest fear is
our stress and our anxiety.

00:51:04.710 --> 00:51:08.430
And more and more people
go crazy about that--

00:51:08.430 --> 00:51:11.520
sometimes, literally, but
mostly figuratively-- and it

00:51:11.520 --> 00:51:14.760
changes our everyday life.

00:51:14.760 --> 00:51:17.970
And we become less
and less happy.

00:51:17.970 --> 00:51:21.000
We need to understand that
to be happy you don't need

00:51:21.000 --> 00:51:25.680
to have a big mansion in
London, or private jet, or even

00:51:25.680 --> 00:51:27.330
a good computer.

00:51:27.330 --> 00:51:30.270
Or even a great job,
or get good salary--

00:51:30.270 --> 00:51:31.185
or even your family.

00:51:34.950 --> 00:51:37.090
What makes you
happy is yourself.

00:51:37.090 --> 00:51:40.300
It's your perception in
your brain, in your soul.

00:51:40.300 --> 00:51:44.740
There are some people who
are happy to have 10 children

00:51:44.740 --> 00:51:46.690
and be happy
fathers and mothers.

00:51:46.690 --> 00:51:48.970
There are people who
are happy to travel

00:51:48.970 --> 00:51:51.190
to the end of their lives
and not have families.

00:51:51.190 --> 00:51:53.480
There are people who
want to have money

00:51:53.480 --> 00:51:55.730
and they are really
happy to have money.

00:51:55.730 --> 00:51:57.680
There are people who don't care.

00:51:57.680 --> 00:52:02.440
But our nowaday narrative
gives less freedom.

00:52:02.440 --> 00:52:04.980
All of us are forced
to live the same lives.

00:52:04.980 --> 00:52:05.950
Here is one.

00:52:05.950 --> 00:52:07.390
You need to have a good salary.

00:52:07.390 --> 00:52:10.510
You to have wife and children,
or husband and children.

00:52:10.510 --> 00:52:14.360
You need to be treated
correctly by society,

00:52:14.360 --> 00:52:16.280
and you need to behave this way.

00:52:16.280 --> 00:52:18.370
You cannot live in the forest.

00:52:18.370 --> 00:52:19.990
You cannot do that.

00:52:19.990 --> 00:52:22.900
But people who lived
300, 400 years ago,

00:52:22.900 --> 00:52:26.620
1,000 years ago, sometimes
they suffered more.

00:52:26.620 --> 00:52:28.180
But were they less happy?

00:52:28.180 --> 00:52:29.800
Or are we more happy?

00:52:29.800 --> 00:52:31.330
I don't think so.

00:52:31.330 --> 00:52:35.110
There are some people who
have serious diseases who are

00:52:35.110 --> 00:52:37.530
happier than healthy people.

00:52:37.530 --> 00:52:41.080
So happiness, I think, is
much more important for us

00:52:41.080 --> 00:52:43.096
than development.

00:52:43.096 --> 00:52:44.470
So we need to
focus on happiness.

00:52:44.470 --> 00:52:51.790
[APPLAUSE]

