SLAVA VAKARCHUK: Good shot.

00:57:26.940 --> 00:57:27.774
AUDIENCE: Hi, Slava.

00:57:27.774 --> 00:57:28.606
SLAVA VAKARCHUK: Hi.

00:57:28.606 --> 00:57:31.230
AUDIENCE: I want to finish on
the question that is actually

00:57:31.230 --> 00:57:34.560
more related to innovations,
and you kind of talked

00:57:34.560 --> 00:57:37.020
about artificial intelligence
and how important it's

00:57:37.020 --> 00:57:38.460
going to be in the future.

00:57:38.460 --> 00:57:42.850
Obviously, it's going to help
us solve simple problems.

00:57:42.850 --> 00:57:45.000
But what about music and arts?

00:57:45.000 --> 00:57:47.910
Do you think it will
overtake the human?

00:57:47.910 --> 00:57:51.690
Or what's the value of
artificially created music

00:57:51.690 --> 00:57:52.860
and art going to be?

00:57:52.860 --> 00:57:55.560
SLAVA VAKARCHUK: I
don't know, exactly.

00:57:55.560 --> 00:57:58.940
I don't know because you
come to a very important

00:57:58.940 --> 00:58:00.780
philosophic question.

00:58:00.780 --> 00:58:04.880
Is art a brain creation?

00:58:04.880 --> 00:58:07.910
Or is art a--

00:58:07.910 --> 00:58:10.130
what we call, a soul creation?

00:58:10.130 --> 00:58:12.200
As a materialist, we
understand that soul

00:58:12.200 --> 00:58:14.810
is a rather abstract thing.

00:58:14.810 --> 00:58:17.630
Although some people can
say that you can derive it

00:58:17.630 --> 00:58:23.180
from our neural system, from
serotonin, and [INAUDIBLE],

00:58:23.180 --> 00:58:24.630
and all these things.

00:58:24.630 --> 00:58:26.840
But I don't know.

00:58:26.840 --> 00:58:30.440
From what I've seen
from first attempts

00:58:30.440 --> 00:58:34.580
to do artificial music, it
sounds clumsy and awkward.

00:58:34.580 --> 00:58:36.650
But it's only the beginning.

00:58:36.650 --> 00:58:39.340
So probably one day
we will start crying

00:58:39.340 --> 00:58:44.120
and we got goosebumps from
music that robots created.

00:58:44.120 --> 00:58:45.980
I don't know.

00:58:45.980 --> 00:58:50.840
You want my fair answer?

00:58:50.840 --> 00:58:53.930
What do I want to see?

00:58:53.930 --> 00:58:57.080
I'm a human being nationalist.

00:58:57.080 --> 00:59:03.010
So I prefer that human beings
create human stuff and robot

00:59:03.010 --> 00:59:05.250
create everything else.

00:59:05.250 --> 00:59:07.010
But I'm not sure that
we'll be like that.

00:59:07.010 --> 00:59:08.570
I don't know.

00:59:08.570 --> 00:59:09.180
SPEAKER: OK.

00:59:09.180 --> 00:59:10.190
So thank you very much.

00:59:10.190 --> 00:59:12.040
[APPLAUSE]

